knowledge_graph.title: Solar energy
knowledge_graph.description: Solar energy is radiant light and heat from the Sun that is harnessed using a range of ever-evolving technologies such as solar heating, photovoltaics, solar thermal energy, solar architecture, molten salt power plants and artificial photosynthesis.

answer_box.title: What is Solar Energy and How Do Solar Panels Work ...
answer_box.snippet: Solar energy works by capturing the sun's energy and turning it into electricity for your home or business. Our sun is a natural nuclear reactor. It releases tiny packets of energy called photons, which travel the 93 million miles from the sun to Earth in about 8.5 minutes.
